Tackle tougher monsters and reap greater rewards.
In a place far away from anywhere else.
You are part of a group of explorers, making your way through the forest.
Feeling a strange presence,* you notice something between the trees.
Drawn to it,* you approach this strange relic and raise a hand towards it.
Upon touching its surface, a blinding light engulfs you.

Desc: As in a piece of block used for building a wall or ground
This category contains objects from mods

English: The resting place of a former adventurer?
An abandoned makeshift tent, who would have lived here?
A tree that grows in the chasms of Azeos Wilderness. It is unknown how far down it reaches.
A lifelike representation of an Acid Larva.
A porous smooth stone, some believe it wards off evil spirits.
An advanced workbench for creating rings and necklaces.
A leatherbound book written in unsteady human language. It appears that the author believed to have found the mythological center of the earth, before succumbing to illness.
Workbench to tinker with the wonders of chemistry.
A technological marvel: an inventory chest from outer space! Seems like even advanced civilizations need to stash things away.
A piece of tech that would still be functional, had it not been ripped out of the floor by greedy hands.
A descriptive stele, carved into mysterious stone. Its meaning is beyond earthly understanding.
A large descriptive stele, carved into mysterious stone. Its meaning is beyond earthly understanding.
It looks like a pillar but its actual function is unknown. Is it a cooling mechanism or does it perhaps store energy?
This airtight jacket keeps the atmosphere around your body evenly pressured and is equipped with a system to increase damage efficiency.
A highly advanced light using a giant ancient gemstone. It almost appears like an oversized torch made for something with even larger hands.
A breakable box that is not from this world. It contains extraterrestrial goods.
A futuristic helm sealed under a big glass dome, leaving the view open to marvel at the miracles of space.
Heavy pants that are less suited for quick movements and more for safely treading on foreign planets.
A piece of alien technology that seems to have burned out.
Solid remains of an ancient forest. The light it reflects is warm and golden.
A perfectly preserved fish egg encapsulated in amber. How those two combined is a mystery.
Grub encapsulated in amber, an extremely rare ingredient.
The petrified shell of an ancient sea creature.
Simple but beautiful necklace featuring a fossil.
This heavy weapon is actually just a ship anchor. Hits very hard and can throw enemies off.
Valuable ancient coin, currency of the underground.
A mysteriously glowing container holding ancient goods.
An unusual feather left by something big.
A very old design for a fishing hook that is not used anymore.
Only those with secret knowledge know where to find this fountain. It is powered by an ammonite fossil that crystalized through the presence of ancient gemstones.
A necklace crafted with only using ancient gemstones as well as a super rare white version.
This shimmering plate has intricate engravings, it looks like a key to something.
This mysterious ring is entirely made out of ancient gemstones, featuring a super rare white one.
This noble robe covers the body in a cascading, silk-like fabric. The woven in ancient gemstone enhance spiritual capabilities.
Strange, blue gemstone emitting waves of energy.
A set of pants that feels very comfortable to wear. Rooting you in the here and now, you can feel your mental focus increasing.
This coin cast in gold seems to be a much older currency than the common ancient coins. It's also worth a whole lot more.
A truly powerful relic of the past, made for fending off the strongest of foes.
A relic that is made in the same way as the Ancient Guardian Necklace, made for fending off the strongest of foes.
A strange device that materializes spirits of the past.
A small wooden box containing all kinds of brushes, pastes and powders that have been used for makeup.
Great architects of the lost civilization must have used this to take down almost any wall in their way.
One of the first weapons ever made by mankind, but this one has an ancient gemstone in place of a normal spearhead.
This moon-blue fish seemed to have had a normal body once, but the water of the Shimmering Frontier corrupted it to be crystalline through and through.
Drenched in blue glaze and stuck with candles, this glow tulip chocolate cake marks a special anniversary.
This blazing blue party hat can be worn to celebrate a special anniversary.
This groovy green party hat can be worn to celebrate a special anniversary.
This perky purple party hat can be worn to celebrate a special anniversary.
This radical red party hat can be worn to celebrate a special anniversary.
An ancient game for two players, there is no rulebook but apparently it was about shifting blocks around.
A plain robe worn by mages in training.
Comfortable and breezy pants that aid in focus.
A cloak with particular magical patterns woven in.
The magic energies around you let you see just as clearly as with your eyes.
Both sturdy and light, these pants won't get in the way while casting spells.
Unleash a torrent of arcane energies.
A hat that's made to go adventuring. Never falls off, even when a giant boulder is chasing behind.
A good pair of pants that is made for traveling long distances and sneaking past ancient traps.
A leather jacket that's almost too warm to wear on adventures, but it looks cool!
This multi-layered piece of fabric is tightly woven to keep the body cool and protect from coarse, grainy sand.
A mysterious hood for true desert dwellers that keeps the face in shade.
Extremely rare type of jellyfish. It almost feels out of this world.
A large chest resembling the slithering giant in the Sunken Sea. Once having been part of this monstrosity allows it to float on the surface of water.

This is but one of the many hundred hearts of the Atlantean Worm that give it the strength to hurl its gigantic body through the water. Therefore it brims with vitality that you can now call your own.
A fierce looking helm that resembles the head of the Atlantean Worm. How it came to be is a mystery.
This organic necklace looks like a miniature version of the Atlantean Worm. Maybe it is a juvenile that would grow to become as large as its origin.
An organic ring that looks like one of the segments of the Atlantean Worm. It must have grown inside its body as an anomaly.
A dislodged, razorsharp mandible of the Atlantean Worm. The maker of the deep sea.
A lifelike representation of the Atlantean Worm.
Forged from a piece of the sky titan's beak.
A beautiful fan created in honor of Azeos that appears to create wind without swinging it. A gift worthy of a queen.
A colorful talon feather from Azeos, the Sky Titan. By holding it you can dash at a high speed.
A lifelike representation of Azeos the Sky Titan.
A beautiful blue fish with scales that look like feathers.
A small bag holding multiple colored marbles made from glass and cheap gemstones. They have probably been used for child's games.
A pointy bait that can stick to fish from the outside to catch more and catch them faster.
A wiggly bait that looks like a red worm, large enough to allow more than one fish to get caught sometimes.
A well-seasoned type of bait that attracts fish more quickly.
An icky type of bait that may stick on to fish that didn't even bite.
A shimmering bait that catches the eye of more rare fish.
A sugary type of bait that increases the chance of catching fish instead of loot.
A luminous type of bait that increases the chance of pulling up loot.
This lure consists of multiple edible and magical components, attracting the one big catch that lingers in deep waters. Is consumed on successful use.
Quite literally a crystal pillar with bait fixed to its top. Placing it in the waters of the Sunken Sea will make the true terror of the deep aware of your presence if close enough.
A fluffy giant spore. It's non-toxic but also not very useful.
A menacing weapon that swings wide and hits hard.
A place to sleep. Also allows friendly inhabitants to move in if placed in a room to their liking.
A simple fork that has seen too much use.
A giant stone tile decorated with a deep blue glass. It depicts a gathering of cavelings.
A giant stone tile decorated with a deep blue glass. It depicts a glowing gemstone.
A giant stone tile decorated with a deep blue glass. It depicts a robed caveling.
A giant jungle tree that seems to have grown from the essence of life itself. A must have decoration.
A lifelike representation of a Big Larva.
A lifelike representation of a Big Dracularva.
A blue swim suit piece that keeps everything in its place. Everyone knows the most revealing armor is the most protective.
A green swim suit piece that keeps everything in its place. Everyone knows the most revealing armor is the most protective.
A red swim suit piece that keeps everything in its place. Everyone knows the most revealing armor is the most protective.
A blue underwear piece that goes well with its top part. Get rid of unnecessary clothing and run free in the sun!
A green underwear piece that goes well with its top part. Get rid of unnecessary clothing and run free in the sun!
A red underwear piece that goes well with its top part. Get rid of unnecessary clothing and run free in the sun!
A mysterious string woven from fine filaments. It can be used to bind a set of cards together.
Scans the world for Azeos the Sky Titan. Consumed on successful scan.
A black variant of the bubble pearl, from certain angles it appears golden.
The black variant of a desert diamond that is highly sought after by miners. It seems to invert reflected light and cast it back as shadows.
A necklace made from pitch-black metal that leaves dark smudges on your neck.
A ring made from pitch-black metal, darkened by the constant presence of immense heat.
A rare sea critter with spikes as hard as steel.
A handful of healthy cereal that fills you up and gives you energy.
A very rare variant of the common bloat oat.
Grows into a filling crop when planted.
Sticky necklace infused with energy made for an unknown purpose.
The crimson remains of someone meeting a terrible fate.
A simple weapon loaded with poisonous darts.
Small, blue fish home to the dirt cave lakes.
This flying bug always appears in swarms which appear as dancing lights. Its blue glow is biome-specific.
A delicate instrument that has multiple fractures across its surface, rendering it unusable. There is a signature reading 'Woopsiee', that has been carved into the glass.
A piece of deep blue glass, it appears to be a fusion of molten sand and ancient gemstones.
A blue lump of marine plants.
A lifelike representation of a slippery Blue Slime.
This wide workstation allows the construction of different boats. Ahoy!
A stronger explosive for crowd control and facing giant enemies.
A fierce vegetable for spicing up foods.
A very rare variant of the common bomb pepper.
Grows into a spicy vegetable when planted.
A ring crowned with a little bomb idol. Handling explosives while wearing it results in an even stronger blast.
A lifelike representation of a Bomb Scarab.
A crude piece of jewelry carved from bone.
A primitive piece of jewelry made from small bones. Early humans have also made these for many different reasons.
A prehistoric, crude ring made from bone. Rings like these have been discovered in early human graves.
A large, ancient chest crested with gemstones.
A bright yellow fish with long barbels that it drags along the sea floor in search for food.
A simple ring that forms a magical veil.
These chocolates come in a nice gift box and are mouth and heart melting.
A bright fish with fiery belly that seems to purely feed from liquid stone and the gemstones caught within.
A broken container made from clay. It was used to carry rations of water across the desert.
A partially broken grave that either survived the currents of time or a quick attempt to gain treasure.
A piece of an ancient weapon. Even though it's only the handle it already feels mysteriously balanced in your hand.
Unstable pillar for decoration, probably thousands of years old.
A leaking wooden ship that is missing its sail.
A good armor to survive battles more easily.
This helm repels slight blows to the head.
This brown, agile fish is able to move between water holes in the desert to change feeding grounds.
A strange ranged weapon that shoots out hovering bubbles, adding slippery movement on contact.
A beautiful, iridescent pearl. It seems to be hollow.
Natural grown jewelry made from rare bubble pearls.
A bucket. The clever solution to transporting water.
This handy tool allows you to catch tiny critters instead of accidentally stepping on them.
This fiery weapon was modeled after the grubzooka but enhanced with lava rock shielding to contain its power. Can blast away stone walls and anything weaker.
A stubby patch of grass to use as a decorative.
A small butterfly with deep red wings that seeks the company of other critters.
An erraticly fluttering butterfly that has bright colors irritating to the naked eye.
Said to be a bringer of good dreams this butterfly is always seen among sleeping creatures.
This blue butterfly flaps its wings so fast that it creates cold air streams.
A tiny butterfly with very delicate wings. Catching it without harming them requires a lot of caution.
A composite material of calcite and fossilized seashells.
A useful calendar that will attract a shady merchant when placed in a habitable room. Depending on the season, he will put on different costumes and offer new items.
Great for huddling together, telling stories and burning marshmallows to a crisp.
This simple decorative candle can be placed anywhere to set up a cozy atmosphere.
A set of candles for your decoration needs or the right atmosphere when summoning evil entities.
An organic body armor resembling Ghorm's shell, it is heavy and feels weird on the inside.
A chitin-plated head piece, wearing it fills you with the urge to dig paths through the darkness.
Rock-hard vegetable that toughens you up.
A very rare variant of the common carrock.
A tough seed that only grows in stone.
A table to share your map discoveries with other explorers.
It looks like an Ancient Gemstone but seems to be extremely dense with energy. Has it been used to grow the Shimmering Frontier?
Useful, handy and secure: the box. One that cattle will feel comfortable to be carried around in and delivered right onto the doorstep of your next farm. Can only be used once.
This useful tray can be filled to the brim with cattle feed to keep cattle fed and happy.
A workbench to create helpful tools and furniture for keeping happy animals.
Odd necklace made from a fish that never let go of the hook.
Every underground miner needs one of those!
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Assassin
Dry, hard bread. It feels like chewing chalk but fills the stomach.
Made from grub leather, good for unhindered movement in combat.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Brute.
A strong, bottled brew made from unknown ingredients. After ingesting it's hard for you to stand still.
A chunky, sweet snack in a wrapper. Must be thousands of years old and probably still edible for a couple more.
This small drinking cup must have held many different beverages. There is still a faint smell of something sweet.
A handmade doll found in a grave. It must once have belonged to a child...
A small depiction of a caveling, it's hollow and must have been used for storing small goods.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Gardener.
A dark version of the ancient floor tiles, it looks much older.
A crumbly stone slab with simple patterns embedded in it.
Light armor hood that hides the face.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Hunter.
A sturdy card that once belonged to a citizen of the forlorn metropolis. It's thousand of years old but the excellent print hasn't faded.
A lifelike representation of a Infected Caveling.
Minted medallion with a face relief. Has it been awarded to someone extraordinary once?
An old crystal ring, holding it fills you with a sad feeling you can't describe.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Mummy.
These pants don't cover much but make your movement more elusive.
A blue fragrance bottle. It is tightly sealed but emits a heavenly scent.
An urn made from stone filled with the belongings of cavelings.
This intricate mask seems to have been worn by an important spiritual figure.
This simple footwear is perfect as a protection against hot desert sand. Unfortunately it's too small to be worn by a human.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Shaman.
An ancient book with stitched blue covers. Is that skin?
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Skirmisher.
Remains of what was once a proud civilization.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling Spearman.
A crude, blocky piece of furniture, many meals must have been shared on it.
This unusual seat is proof of an empire fallen to ruin.
Between mining there must be time for serious business.
A lifelike representation of a Caveling.
An ancient, precious instrument but it is clogged.
An unpredictable, powerful weapon that weaves chaotic ancient energy into all kinds of projectiles. The enemy will never know what's coming for them.
A small skull burnt dark to the marrow. Exposure to intense heat for a long time causes something like this to happen.
This box contains a strange, synthetic food source that doesn't appear safe for human consumption.
A super sweet candy that ends up in the gap of your teeth. And it's there to stay.
Made with some of the finest Bambuck wool.
This grand headdress shows clearly who's boss.
Fine shorts with plenty of jewelry, well suited for a leader.
While this golden coin holds many favorable meanings, the most important one is that it can be spent at a certain merchant.
An imposing monument to be placed in front of entrances, meant to keep figures with ill intent away.
Woven from woolen string, this decoration symbolizes good luck, prosperity and abundance.
A cozy light that can create a warm atmosphere in any room. It even comes in different colors.
A set of small lanterns that go nicely on the walls. Just like their bigger counterparts, they exist in many different colors.
An old stone plate. What kind of food has been served on it?
A lifelike representation of a Bakery Brute.
A lifelike representation of a Gingerbreadling.
This fireplace is a great addition to every base when it's cold outside. Crackling fire and the smell of burning wood add to a homely atmosphere.
A mix of colorful lights to decorate the walls with.
Small colorful lights to decorate the walls with.
A mysterious golden gift with unknown contents. Rip it open and peek inside!
A mysterious gift with unknown contents. Rip it open and peek inside!
A lifelike representation of a Starwand Shaman.
A lifelike representation of a Santa Shrooman.
A lifelike representation of a Snowhead Slime.
A cold fellow that came into existence by stacking large snowballs together. Keep it around to not feel as lonely anymore.
A lifelike representation of a Carrot Slime.
A nice little stool that goes well with a richly decorated table. It's hard to sit still on it when opening presents is due.
This big table serves as a nice basis to set up a great dinner and bring the family together.
Celebrating the cold season is not complete without setting up one of these. The centerpoint of every well-decorated lawn or living room.
This simple wreath will do nicely on any wall and show visitors that its finally holiday.
A cozy sock to put on the wall. By tradition these were filled with small trinkets and candy.
Two crossed candy canes that are rather for decoration, not consumption. Put them on the wall for a nice winter flair.
Two wintry candles sitting on a candle dish, made to be put on the wall. Careful with the fire, though.
A delicate snowflake that will look great on the walls of your home.
This crafting table is perfect to create holiday decorations for the cold season.
Icky groundcover that feels strange to walk across. Larvas will infest chrysalis-covered areas over time.
Ground plants found in the forlorn metropolis. They grow tiny berries that attract cavelings of the corresponding area.
This precious container holds useful items that have been used by citizens of the ancient city.
A load-bearing pillar which holds up the foundation of the forlorn Metropolis.
Ground plants found in the Clay Caves. They grow aromatic berries that attract cavelings of the corresponding area.
A crude container thats already almost broken. Smash it to relieve it of its contents.
A lifelike representation of a Clay Burrower.
A blood-red ring that latches onto your finger.
A lifelike representation of a cocoon.
The cast-off husk of a giant insect that lives dormant in the ground for centuries. When it emerges to take on its final form, heavy earthquakes occur.
A lifelike representation of a Colossal Amoeba.
A knife attached to a wrist band hidden among layers of fabric. It's perfect for an unsuspected stealth attack.
A beautiful necklace featuring a small shell. When you hold it up to your ear you can hear distant waves.
The hallmark of every professional cook. Proof that even in the undergrounds taste can have priority over nutrition.
Sporting an apron, these pants are made to prove their worth in the steam and heat of a cave kitchen.
It's just a spotless, white jacket but the red neckerchief makes it official. Time to get cookin'!
To trade with the one that decides who is naughty and who is nice.
Only the ones really passionate about cooking dare to become the pot itself.
Cooking ingredients brings out their full potential. Combine two and see what happens!
A shiny metal cover that suppresses your boiling point.
Get started with creating armor for looks and combat.
A simple metal ingot for blacksmithing.
Got no sixpack? Just craft one!
A crude chest made from copper. It is not locked anymore.
This pendant sharpens the focus, allowing for more precise hits.
Resembles more of a bucket but repels strong blows to the head.
A sturdy tool to prepare ground for farming. Covers an area of 2x2 tiles.
A crude key cast in copper. There should be a lock somewhere that it fits into.
A sturdy tool, well-suited for breaking down walls effortlessly.
A sturdy shovel, good for digging up ground.
A good weapon for smashing foes and walls.
A good weapon for slaying foes.
A versatile workbench to prepare you for the underground world.
A necklace made with a pretty coral badge and white pebbles.
A shimmering bridge supported by coral pillars that are reaching down into the sea ground.
A neat little fence made from pink corals.
A fitting gate for the coral fence.
A floor made from little organic tiles and differently colored sea floor pebbles.
Coral wood slate for more precise carpentry work.
An intricate ring naturally grown from pink, branchy corals.
Once planted it spreads corals in every direction. Can only be planted on beach sand.
A red type of coral that is great for crafting.
Crystal idol to reawaken the Core Commander. Consumed upon placing it on the Core Commander's summoning rune.
An astonishing upper body armor that sends pulses of energy through the body. It feels almost forbidden to wear it, brimming with more power than a human body could potentially handle.
A chest that seems to have been the black box of an alien ship.
The discarded headpiece of a high-rank armor. When worn, you can feel an immense power surging through your mind. It's whispering words you could never understand.
Woven from otherworldly cloth in confusing patterns, this armor piece escapes any understanding of earthly craftsmanship.
A lifelike representation of the Core Commander.
A manufactured crystal that looks like the eye of the core. This one is raw and unfinished, as if something interrupted the process.
This blue slate depicts a graph of a sudden spike in energy levels before collapsing.
This blue slate depicts a graph of a disturbance in previous patterns resulting in more advanced processes.
This blue slate depicts a graph of an entity redistributing processing power from multiple sources.
A lifelike representation of the core.
A simple tunic but with jewelry and fine fabrics layered on top.
A wooden mask with decorative beads and a distant stare.
A pair of shorts, decorated with various bands and jewelry.
An aromatic snack that seems out of this world. Is it proof that the moon is made out of cheese after all?
A strange entity that is unlike any terrestrial sea life you have ever seen. Did it come from a place far away from earth?
The innocent juvenile of a Moolin, who has just learned how to stand on its own hoofs. It grows up faster than you think, so give it all the love you have.
Home to the meadows, this violet bovine is living its life away from danger, happily grazing all day and producing some of the finest milk.
A lifelike representation of a bubble crab.
Grants the bearer access to deeper wellsprings of power.
Allows the bearer to reach further sources of wisdom.
This tiny bug appears in many different places. Right now it's looking for a new home.
This desert critter has an unknown amount of legs. It would simply take too long to count them.
A disgusting insect that moves with uncanny speed. It commonly is found in places that have darkness, dirt and food to offer.
This red-yellow crustacean always has its claws raised which gives it a seemingly happy expression.
This blue-purple crustacean always has its claws raised which gives it a seemingly happy expression.
A very nervous little fellow. The faintest hint of danger makes it jump away into safety.

Desc: Except for Englisch and German it should be translated as 'Small Larva'

English: A tiny larva that doesn't harm you but likes to be collected and held in a warm hand.
A dark fellow with seemingly unseeing eyes. But they stare deep into your soul.
This luminous dweller drifts through the air like a calm breath, even in the most impetuous areas.
This small scorpion is harmless to humans but can easily kill smaller creatures if it needs food.
Frantically flying around, this little mosquito pokes at other lifeforms for a potential drop of blood.
A small snail that slowly works its way through the dangers of the Shimmering Frontier.
A worm. Nothing special about it.
Separates horizontal and vertical wires. Useful to allow crossing wires without connecting the electricity. Direction of connections can be changed by interacting with the circuit.
All hail the pale king of water!
Can very slowly drill through tougher materials such as ore boulders when powered with electricity. Drills drilling together yield better results.
All that's left of a creature that had the misfortune to stumble upon the Shimmering Frontier.
A crystalline piece of equipment that shields the upper body like a fortress. The bright material evokes old memories of the sun.
A rare specimen of a colossal cicada that would have become a titan. But due to becoming corrupted with crystals inside its husk, it died when it tried to finally emerge.
A shimmering surface that attracts lifeforms found in crystalline environments.
A fragile crystal growth that shimmers like the sun. You can see items encased within.
A nearly indestructible helm forged with patience and precision. When it is worn, you feel energized, lively and protected.
A crystallized lump of marine plants.
This tall torch seems to generate fire from transforming the energy of an ancient gemstone.

Desc: Nilipede can be translated as anything millipede/centipede + words relating to darkness

English: A highly advanced piece of technology that stores nuclear energy. When placed in a habitable room, it will attract a bold traveler of the Shimmering Frontier.
This piece is merely a fraction of an enormous ancient gemstone.
A very big ancient gemstone fused from smaller shards. It emits a strange energy that makes you feel nauseous and feverish.
A captivating necklace that catches your enemies off-guard so that they lower their defense. Unfortunately it has the same effect on you.
Heavy hip protection made from miraculous materials. When it is worn, you feel guided along a path to victory.
A captivating ring that catches your enemies off-guard so that they lower their defense. Unfortunately it has the same effect on you.
The leftovers of a crude prehistoric weapon made with an ancient gemstone. It may have helped early humans to hunt more effectively.
A small orb made from deep-blue glass. Its purpose is unknown.
A naturally-grown pillar that rises up from the crystalline depths of the Shimmering Frontier.
A golden-colored glass star for decorating the base in a festive fashion. Better not drop it.
The crystallized, makeshift resting place of a former explorer. They don't have much use for each other anymore.
Crystal clear water that has been filtered through ancient gemstones.
A bow that hits right into the heart of its target and has a chance to infatuate it with the archer.
When wearing this tunic, one feels as if they have been sent from the heavens to spread love.
Dark fluid from an oversized amoeba.
The scales of this fish are thin like razorblades.
A dark blue lump of marine plants.
A dark fish with fiery belly that seems to purely feed from liquid stone and the gemstones caught within.
A stone disc with peculiar engravings, it must contain mysterious records.
Adding a plant to it will make for a nice decoration.
A safer, better-looking alternative to crude torches.
A thin glass tablet that displays a map of unfamiliar star constellations.
A crystal-plated predator that slithers through the glowing waters of the Shimmering Frontier, always on the hunt for something weaker.
Stores electricity input and sends it out during intervals of 1 second.
A golden breastplate with loose fabric sewn to it that makes you feel like a stealthy warrior of the desert.
A dry bush that can live hundreds of years without water.
Ground plants found in the Desert of Beginnings. They grow fragrant flowers that attract cavelings of the corresponding area.
A dry plant containing natural loot from the desert.
A very rare crystal sparkling with a beautiful white light.
A crimson gemstone rarely found in crystalized dry regions. Its special properties allow it to be used for higher quality crafting.
A mysterious piece of equipment with a golden mask. It seems to have been granted to warriors of high rank.
Wide harem pants made for fighting, coupled with a set of pointy golden shoes.
A large sandstone arc, you're not exactly sure how it fits in your backpack.
A large sandstone arc, you're not exactly sure how it fits in your backpack.
A giant sandstone arc, you're not exactly sure how it fits in your backpack.
A giant sandstone arc, you're not exactly sure how it fits in your backpack.
An ancient crate filled with goods of an old desert civilization.
A hellspawn that dwells in the sea ground. Don't step on it.
This beverage made from rare pink slime tastes like cotton sugar and makes your heart flutter.
A workbench to produce more advanced potions.
An upper body armor made from long kelp strands. Now you feel like a real creature of the sea.
This heavy chunk of metal was used to explore deep waters, unfortunately it's leaking now. Still works as a nice armor piece.
A true trinket of the sea, made from kelp and a trident pendant. Mistaking you for a mythic sea ruler, fish come to you more often.
Squeaky footwear made from a rubber-like material. It's uncomfortably wet.
A quite lively little ring that tries to swim off of your finger. By the time it realizes it's merely a ring it has already forgot about it again.
A cute chick full of determination to one day become a graceful dodo. It struggles with the size of its beak.
Long believed to be extinct this species is still thriving in the underground: the dodo! If only Darwin could have seen this...
This ring is made to be put an two fingers at the same time. Revolutionary.
An intimidating but well-meaning mask that invokes the spirit of mythological dragons.
Allows changing the equipment shown on your character.
A simple stool made with beach materials.
Someone made this from materials floating in the water.
Can slowly drill through tougher materials such as ore boulders when powered with electricity. Drills drilling together yield better results.
A powerfull tool to cut through weaker walls like butter.
A powered up hand drill, ready to tear down stronger walls without struggle.
A dead insect void of any moisture. It is nice to look at but needs to be handled with care.
This tight pack of explosives can be detonated in safety with an external trigger.
A squarish earring plated with gold.
Remains of a human that lived about 200.000 years ago. Has mankind found these caves before?
A unique lifelike representation of the Awakened Azeos.
A unique variant of the large ancient chest.
A derpy-looking chicken hat that will be center of attention at the next party. Clucking funny!
These flashy pants are chicken skin-inducing and complete the look of an egg-citing easter costume.
Itchy feathers and a concerning lack of ventilation make this chicken body piece a bold choice of clothing.
A handful of daisies, made to sprinkle some spring onto the floor. One package is enough to cover a 1x1 ground tile.
An icky collectible egg that can be used as currency for a certain merchant. Get as many as you can, they might not be around for long.
A dirty collectible egg that can be used as currency for a certain merchant. Get as many as you can, they might not be around for long.
Greenery and daisies pop out of this egg-shaped flowerpot. They resemble the awakening of spring.
Illuminate your base with this decorative lamp, featuring a golden easter egg sitting in a nest of greenery.
A weedy collectible egg that can be used as currency for a certain merchant. Get as many as you can, they might not be around for long.
A rocky collectible egg that can be used as currency for a certain merchant. Get as many as you can, they might not be around for long.
Everyone wearing this oversized egg shell hat has only one mission: to become egg.
These cheaply made pants are as yellow as egg yolk and itchy beyond comprehension.

Desc: Any translations of the word 'eggcellent' should be 'Egg' + 'positive word' in other languages.
English: A spacious, oval shape that is made from hopes, dreams and lime. In other words: Egg.
This charming green garland is adorned with little daisies, making it a perfect addition to your Easter-themed walls.
A golden crystalline egg. It might be used for something more than just decoration...
Sitting on this stool feels as if sitting on a freshly cut meadow. There is no better spot to place ones bottoms.
Lay out your belongings on this soft, overgrown table that fits every nature-themed base.
A small 1x1 table made from creme-colored stone and a little leaf as cover. Simple, practical and still in line with the Easter spririt.
A beautiful decorative pillar, holding up high a planter containing spring flowers. A perfect way to greet the new season.
This small working table contains the right materials to create a selection of spring and Easter-themed decorations.
A creaking chest, useful for storing belongings. There are faint growling noises that can be heard from inside.
Years of misuse turned this dresser into what it is now. Hopefully it treats your clothes better.
Dark floor boards trodden for many years by unholy feet.
An old rug with a mysterious sigil. A witness of too many séances.
A seating opportunity made from cursed wood, ready to scare your buttocks off.
An old table that was used to serve horrible dishes. The presence of those who devoured them still lingers.
A torch that stands like an eerie beacon in the darkness of the caves.
A large egg protected by an ivory shell. Safe for consumption!
This device is made to hatch mysterious eggs. Please don't exceed the recommended temperature.
A draconic fish that is several hundred years old. The verdant color of its scales has long faded.
Opens up when powered with electricity.
Connects sources of electricity to machines and apparatuses.
Powers wires and objects with electricity.
Emits a very low electricity that is too low to power up objects but useful to change behavior of logic circuits.
Workbench to create electrical and logical systems.
The ashen remains in it hint at it once being used to harden metals in its fires over a long period of time.
A beautiful green fish with scales that look like feathers.
Its emptiness is proof of the blasphemous acts of grave raiders.

Desc: It's a reference to The Beauty and the Beast. The German translation has a different wording to resemble the German phrase used in the film regarding the curse of the enchanted rose. Please try to treat it equally for other languages, might need a bit of research
English: To love another and earn their love in return.
This incredible device is able to weave free matter into a temporary living being when charged with electricity. Requires a figurine as blueprint.
Ancient water is encapsulated in this beautiful crystal. It's been in there for millions of years.
A strong elixir that buffs your muscles and your temper.
A curved twig holding a golden egg at its end. It is a sign of renewal and fertility.
The most wicked creation of all, its taste an insult to the living. Black licorice.
A simple backpack made for traveling the underground caves. Holds quite a few items.
A status symbol among tribal cavelings. You can sense blood lust from the loose tooth.
Tuck a straw in your mouth and get ready for a whole day of relaxing on the porch.
Scale of the Feather Fish, it is sturdy but as light as a feather.
Not a tree at all, but a tall invertebrate feeding on floating particles with its long arms.
Not a tree at all, but a tall invertebrate feeding on floating particles with its long arms.
Silky-smooth material for creating fabric and armor.
A magical staff that the caveling shamans use in their rituals and against uninvited guests.
This giant firework rocket needs some time to take off but rewards patience with a spectacular explosion. Can be set off by using a torch or electricity on it.
A firework rocket that flies up and results in a blue explosion when ignited, perfect for all kinds of celebration. Can be set off by using a torch or electricity on it.
A firework rocket that flies up and results in a green explosion when ignited, perfect for all kinds of celebration. Can be set off by using a torch or electricity on it.
A firework rocket that flies up and results in a purple explosion when ignited, perfect for all kinds of celebration. Can be set off by using a torch or electricity on it.
A firework rocket that flies up and results in a red explosion when ignited, perfect for all kinds of celebration. Can be set off by using a torch or electricity on it.
A firework rocket that flies up and results in a yellow explosion when ignited, perfect for all kinds of celebration. Can be set off by using a torch or electricity on it.
The imprint of an ancient fish on a rock slate.
A loose net thrown across some stakes to dry in the air.
A useful workbench to create all kinds of fishing baits with beneficial effects.
A bubbly stone that is as clear as water. It weighs almost nothing.
A mysterious necklace with a burning pendant. It glows intensively but doesn't scorch the skin.
This strange ring produces a flame that affects anything but its wearer.
A flesh-colored lump of marine plants.
Can't argue much with a handful of lead coming right at you.
A soft pillow that can be placed on the ground to sit down on it.
Canned meal made to last for years. You should look for better food options soon.
A trident-shaped coral, not very valuable but nice to look at.
A lifelike representation of a Frankenbrute.
Put more head on your head. Doesn't necessarily add up to more brain, though.
A gemstone that is shaped like crystalline fire.
A pure explosion of flavours enters your mouth when biting into these fruits.
A traditionally baked fruit bread with powdered sugar on top. One slice is never enough!
Rotten with mold down to the marrow, its owner must have suffered greatly.
Groundcover interspersed with mycelium. Over time mushrooms and shroomen will grow on it.
This standard furnace melts basic metal ores.
An unstable forge producing incredible heat able to smelt the hardest of metals.
Looks like a failed experiment to create a new type of alloy. It is too hard to be usable in any way.
A misshappen necklace that combines chunks of all kinds of materials.
A special anvil for creating otherworldly equipment.
An otherworldly ingot for outstanding blacksmithing.
A futuristic protection for the upper body. Its intimidating yet elegant design is a true marvel to look at.
An otherworldly bridge that feels like walking on a path through the universe.
This unique throwing weapon requires finesse and dexterity to be used to its full potential.
An indestructible chest made from galaxite. It is not locked anymore.
A quick-stabbing weapon made for close combat. The blade is so fine that it can cut a hair into two pieces lengthways.
An otherworldly, elegant fence for keeping your base safe.
An otherworldly, elegant gate for the galaxite fence.
An otherworldly tool for pulling up rare fish. Able to withstand great heat.
An otherworldly floor that feels like walking on the night sky.
A futuristic helmet fit for a space explorer. Looking through its visor is like looking into the depths of the universe.
An indestructible key cast in galaxite. There should be a lock somewhere that it fits into.
An otherworldly tool for breaking down exceptionally hard walls.
Otherworldly ore commonly found in sandstone walls.
A futuristic armor for the lower body. It makes you feel like every small step you take is a giant leap for mankind.
An otherworldly shovel, outstanding at digging up ground.
An otherworldly weapon for smashing foes and walls.
An otherworldly weapon for slaying foes.
This high-tech trap shoots out a jet of energy that burns with different temperatures, resulting in a rainbow flame.
An automated high-tech gun that shoots enemies it faces with energy projectiles. Requires electricity to function.
Otherworldly workbench that helps tremendously to survive in the deepest caves.
This rare crab has ancient gemstones growing all over it.
Half of a rock with beautiful crystals inside.
A cleanly cut half of a geode. The simple wooden construction underneath allows it to be attached to a wall.
A plated chest reminiscent of the devourer.
A lifelike representation of Ghorm the Devourer.
A well-preserved stomach portion of the Devourer, comes with a handy strap.
A lifelike representation of a Spookaveling.
A cheap last-minute attempt to get ready for the spooky season.
A big bacterium wiggling around in your hand, fascinating and gross at the same time.
A motionless crimson critter. It just sits there...watching...
This supersized organelle is a real powerhouse.
The king of all mushrooms, growing in perfect conditions made it unusually large.
A sensory organ of a big sea creature. It probably was lost in a fight to death with something even bigger.
A tasty breast armor made from gingerbread, comes with sugar buttons and a fondant bowtie.
A sweet chest made with a sturdy baked body and sugar decor. Perfect to store some seasonal items!
This gingerbread headpiece has not been baked, so it remains flexible to be drawn over the head.
A funny headpiece made from gingerbread. Just ignore the creepy smile and soulless eyes.
Fairly stiff legs are the main feature of this baked armor, as wells as crumbs bewteen the toes.
A transparent bridge that has no supports and that can be built across water or chasms.
This piece of glass can be used as a base material to create more advanced glass objects.
A see-through tile to provide a crystal-clear vision of the ground underneath.
This handy furnace can turn any sand block into useful glass.
This bold statue serves as an art piece that puts the shiny properties of glass on display.
This workbench makes it possible to form glass into more advanced objects to add to your base.
A sugar-covered heart berry that's still juicy and fresh underneath. Delicious!
Once planted it spreads glowing roots in every direction. Can only be planted on crystal ground.
An enigmatic bridge that floats in space and that can be built across water or chasms.
A piece of glowing, crystallized wood that serves as an outstanding crafting material.
An unyielding door to keep adversaries at bay.
A pale, elegant fence for keeping your base safe.
A pale, elegant gate for the gleam wood fence.
An enigmatic floor decorated with patterned tiles.
A luminous wood slate for splendid carpentry work.
A luminous ring that holds the essence of glow tulips.
A branching type of coral that gets its energy through the glowing waters of the Sunken Sea.
A precious, shimmering flower that absorbed ancient energy.
A very rare variant of the common glow tulip.
Grows into a luminescent flower when planted.
A slimy, melting chest that remained from the Abominous Mass.
A lifelike representation of Glurch the Abominous Mass.
A long crafting table to engineer fast vehicles for your travels.
Not (yet) as stubborn as its parents, this kid is mostly concerned with charging at butterflies while its oversized ears flop around in the breeze. Truly a heartwarming sight to behold.
The fuzzy Bambuck has more wool than patience, which is why it's quite bold by nature. It doesn't even see that much, so if it runs into you by accident be easy on it.
A unique, royal piece of armor resembling the heart of the state. Golden wings were added to inherit the grace of Azeos. Before it could be used, the kingdom crumbled to dust from the inside.
A unique, royal piece of armor resembling the head of the state, crowning it as a descendant of the gods. It was intended for a future that never came.

A unique, royal piece of armor resembling the heir of the state, which was supposed to carry the glory of the kingdom when inheriting the throne. A dark prophecy and act of assassination ended the royal line.
A soft metal ingot for blacksmithing and jewelry.
A shiny trinket combining the most valuable of materials.
A precious ring featuring ancient gemstones.
Rarely found in clay and stone walls.
This sun-golden fish seemed to have had a normal body once, but the water of the Shimmering Frontier corrupted it to be crystalline through and through.
An intricate mask with a stern expression, it was probably used in a ritual or by someone of high ranks.
A limited edition chocolate for the cold season. There is no golden ticket inside, instead the whole thing is made out of it!
A gold-plated chrysalis, this doesn't seem to be its final form.
A Solarite-plated predator that slithers through the glowing waters of the Shimmering Frontier, always on the hunt for something weaker.
It's big and shiny, a must have for collectors.
This rare jellyfish seems to do well without water and apparently it likes your company.
Rare, golden variant of larva meat, with increased effects.
This little treasure was used to hold the robe of a caveling scholar in place.
This beautiful bouquet made from golden roses will elevate the look of every room. Give it to someone you like dearly.
This golden ring is very uncomfortable to wear but it looks really cool.
A razorsharp ocean critter polished clean by currents.
This elusive fish appears in swarms as a spectacle of flickering gold to confuse predators.
A small golden whistle with unknown purpose. The sounds it emits is almost unnoticable.
A cumbersome but sturdy armor piece of finely chiselled stone.
The detached head of a core sentry. Wearing it feels incredibly clunky and heavy but it makes up for it with great protection.
Bulky legwear sculpted from solid rock. The best way to train the calves.
The discarded breast piece of a core sentry. It has just the right size to be used as a great shield and the ancient gemstone in its center sometimes shoots out energy as it blocks enemy attacks.
A lifelike representation of a core sentry.

Less like a chest and more like a living organism.

Proof of a once flourishing environment.

This small wooden frame made use of even the tiniest larva to turn its skin into leather.

Golden pieces that once seemed to be fused together to endure great pressure. Something inherently powerful must have broken them apart.

A piece of an ancient weapon. Even though it is of the same material as ancient gemstones, this one feels unnaturally clear and infused with a strange energy.
An unusually well preserved piece of ancient paper. The runes are impossible to decipher but small symbols hint at it being the recipe for a strange weapon.
Generates a low amount of electricity that can be turned on and off.
Augmented by a mysterious energy, this weapon unleashes chaining arcs of lightning upon your foes. Holding it sends a tingling sensation through your arms.

A side-formation of the Amalgam Basin that gets rid of built up heat.
The mutated offspring of its extinct ancestor. Its grey shell had adapted to withstand extreme pressure.

Electricity can move through the circuit when it receives electricity on exactly 2 out of 3 inputs.
This archaic device makes it possible to turn fiber into beautiful clothing and costumes.

Desc: A decorative flooring item like bricks or stone plates, they can change design a bit depending on what the player color them hence why we don't call it just 'stone plates' or so

English: A collection of workable groundcover made from clay. A true hobbyist might turn them into different shapes and colors.
Somewhere someone must paddle around in circles.
What once seemed to have been a normal tree got permeated by crystals, turning it into a living work of art.
A cheaply made ring from a vending machine. If you believe hard enough you may feel more lucky.

CSD!3!? – It's Dangerous To Go Alone
