A mysterious, pointy-eared egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, pointy-eared egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
A scorching little friend that is ready for adventures underground.
A mysterious, transparent egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, transparent egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
A friendly companion from the moldy habitat. Its silky wings are not fit for battle but it will support you from a safe distance.
A mysterious, mold-covered egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, mold-covered egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
A poisonous little friend that is ready for adventures underground.
A mysterious, transparent egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, transparent egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
A royal little friend that is ready for adventures underground.
A mysterious, transparent egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, transparent egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
It's Bob the pet rock. Don't drop or throw him, he has feelings too.
An oozy little friend that is ready for adventures underground.
A mysterious, transparent egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, transparent egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
A slippery little friend that is ready for adventures underground.
A mysterious, transparent egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, transparent egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
This supersized relative of the tardigrade loves to nap in the loose sediment of the Passage. Its upbringing in a harsh environment made it an able defender, too.
A mysterious, mutli-layered egg that is about to hatch.
A mysterious, multi-layered egg that seems to react to your presence. Is there a way to hatch it?
A precious ring that has naturally grown in the yellow blossoms of the jungle caves.
Grey and porous piece of a giant eco system. The ocean it belonged to seems long gone.
Fossilized egg shell, it feels light and brittle.
The fossil of a long gone critter species. They are ancestors of a big variety of lifeforms.
A juicy, sweet fruit that clears your mind and raises focus.
A very rare variant of the common pewpaya.
Grows into a juicy fruit when planted in beach sand.
The top part of an iron pickaxe that is partially molten. It must have been broken while working under extreme conditions.
Undigested remains of prey that could double down as food for fish. Place it in a habitable room and a character interested in fishing may move in.
An intensely tasty fruit that has you clench your weapons tightly.
A very rare variant of the common pinegrapple.
Grows into a refreshing sour and sweet fruit when planted in beach sand.
A vibrant pink blossom that fell from a 'weeping' tree. Its short-lived blooming period reminds one of the transcience of life.
This 'weeping' tree holds its branches low, letting the blossoms droop towards the ground. It is said that brave warriors took depictions of those trees with them into their final battle.
A small pink amphibian with outward-protruding gills that look like corals. It also uses them to draw nutrients out of the waters of the Sunken Sea.
A pink, odd-looking fish with weirdly shaped fins.
This beautiful bouquet made from pink roses will elevate the look of every room. Give it to someone you like dearly.
This little pink creature is entirely translucent with no visible brain. It seems unbothered being held.
An eerie beaked mask. Its inside reeks of rancid death, yet lets you live to smell it.
Wooden slate made for more precise carpentry work.
This wide, stone-hewn box holds up three plants for decoration.
Now that the worst is over, use it to decorate!
A playing dice with unique symbols on each face. It's probably been used in sets and for multiple different games.
A bundle of leaves that grows on plume trees.
This tree has rock-hard bark and deep roots to gain and hold water from the desert grounds. Its leaves grow in puffy bundles.
A purple, mucky liquid that tastes horrible but cures any poison.
Scans the world for Ivy the Poisonous Mass. Consumed on successful scan.
A purple blob of toxic slime. Can be further processed.
A mechanical spike trap that reacts to anyone stepping on it and additionally applies poison when inflicting damage.
A shield covered in toxic grime. Has a chance to poison enemies when blocking attacks.
Farming tool that turned into a weapon when a great threat had to be slain.
This pendant sharpens the focus, allowing for more precise hits.
A necklace made with a pretty coral badge and white pebbles.
A luminous ring that holds the essence of glow tulips.
A shiny trinket combining the most valuable of materials.
A precious ring featuring ancient gemstones.
This golden ring is very uncomfortable to wear but it looks really cool.
A heavy piece of jewelry that increases defence.
A strange ring that pulls in loot around you in a higher radius. Magnets, how do they work?
A necklace made from pure octarine filled with magic energy.
A ring made from pure octarine enhanced with magic properties.
The scarlet variant of an iron chunk necklace. It raises your defense even more and gives additional benefits.
A mirror-like smooth shell that was ground down by currents and swirling sand from the sea ground.
Wearing this winged ring creates a slight wind that pushes you forward.
Allows teleporting to waypoints and portals that have been placed out. The portal takes 10 minutes to charge up before it can be used once it has been placed.
This brittle clay container is just your size and usually filled with caveling supplies.
A heavy clay cover that has partially cracked and doubles down as a funny hat.
It is not an actual flower but a hologram of one. Is it proof of a dying world where nothing grew anymore?
A bonsai-sized offshoot of the common cherry tree, planted in a decorative vase.
A potted shrub on which beautiful flowers grow. It seems to only exist in this form.
A potted shrub on which glowing flowers grow. It seems to only exist in this form.
A bonsai-sized offshoot of the common meadow tree, planted in a wooden pot.
A decorative version of the common Land Algae, planted in a driftwood pot.
A shrub of the magnificient Lucent Oak, growing from a naturally formed crystal pot.
A tree that grows in the chasms of Azeos Wilderness, planted in a clay pot.
A shrub of the common Lush Tree, planted in a makeshift stone pot.
A rare, decorative strain of a Glow Tulip that can withstand tremendous heat.
A bonsai-sized offshoot of the common plume tree, planted in an ancient pot.
An oversized, puffy flower that has been infested with mold.
A pretty decorative without any cracks and blemishes but its original contents are long gone.
Generates a low amount of electricity when stepped on by the player.
An ancient vehicle built by the lost civilization, seemingly for pure fun. It provides only a fraction of the speed it once was capable of.
This intricate, golden chip seems technically very advanced and must have computed complex calculations.
A rhombus-shaped crystal made from glass that has complex circuits embedded. It seems powered down, maybe it could be fed data to activate it again?
A reactivated key belonging to a wise leader. It may open the door to something very valuable.
A moldy fungus fit for gourmets.
A very rare variant of the common puffungi.
A seed that only grows in mold.
Electricity moves through in intervals of 1 second.
A mischievous-looking coin that can be traded for various, eerie goods.
A lifelike representation of a Pumpking Caveling.
A fruit head with a carved-in face. For how disgusting it feels from the inside, it looks pretty cool on the outside.
A scary, yet cozy lantern carved from a fruit. Don't smash it, it brings bad luck.
An odd, ornate ring. You feel a closer bond with your minions whilst wearing it.
A lifelike representation of a poisonous Purple Slime.
A complex wind-up machine created in honor of Ra-Akar that seems to have a mind of its own. A gift worthy of a young prince.
A necklace of the desert with a strong resemblance of the sand titan. Wearing it grants you additional protection and extra damage.
A lifelike representation of Ra-Akar, the Sand Titan.
Whatever the problem is, encountering it behind a protective suit makes it a little less stressful.
A culmination of radioactive elements that resulted in a glass-like structure.
Need to handle strange materials that emit even stranger radiation? Ask no more!
A protective suit is not complete without some boots that save the feet.
A cute hood featuring white rabbit ears. You feel quite cheeky and swift wearing it.
A cute headband featuring white rabbit ears. You feel quite cheeky and swift wearing it.
Traverse the underground world much faster.
Advanced forge to create underground rail systems.
Sticky things slide right off from this glossy elastic coat. The bright yellow is just a nice touch.
Smooth slime-proof boots that keep your feet dry and agile. Also great for jumping into puddles.
A super rare mutation of common kelp, showing off a variety of colors.
Green and full of sweat this piece of clothing is perfect for emerging from the shadows guns blazing.
The only thing you need to put on when you want to rush through the jungle as a one-man-army…wait, that was something else.
Camouflaged leggings that keep you on your toes around heavily-guarded areas.
A light tunic with a quiver allowing for swift archery.
A dark hood of old cloth. Hardly anything but eyes set on your target peep through.

Desc: Changed 'boots' to 'pants' in the description
English: These sturdy leather pants tighten your stance and grant you steady aim for your target.
A four-bladed throwing weapon that bounces back and forth across the room. Slicing any enemy in its path.
Teleports you back to the core, consumed in the process.
A gift to symbolize good wishes and luck for the year ahead. Someone left it for you to open.
This flying bug always appears in swarms which appear as dancing lights. Its red glow is biome-specific.
A red lump of marine plants.
A lifelike representation of an aggressive Red Slime.
Jewelry made from a rare plant that repels poison.
An off-road vehicle that provides quick acceleration but lower top-speed. It looks slightly busted but lets you take curves in a more stable manner.
A peculiar handheld device, used for short range teleportation.
An extraordinary creature that doesn't seem to be from this world. Its biology works entirely different from anything you know.
Simple ring found in the deepest of rocks.
A strange ring made from sand that is held together by the currents of time.
Simple ring carved out of stone.
This unusual dagger is made from a big gemstone shard. There are dark red spots on the handle.
An ancient chalice made from stone and gems. Its insides are layered with dark red residue.
Mechanical helping hand, grabs things and puts them elsewhere when powered with electricity.
A small shark that can break almost every material with one bite.
The young version of a Strolly Poly. Unlike its grown up parents, this one is in constant danger of being stepped on or being mistaken for a larva by careless explorers.
Content with everything going on around it, this gentle giant waddles through the darkness, always in search of a skittering, crunchy snack. Did you know that it is not even an insect?

Desc: Item received from a big roly poly animal. Translations of said animal should refer to something correlating to a roly poly + slowness/wandering/strolling

English: A cast-off plate that makes up the hard armor of a Strolly Poly. Very sturdy and great for crafting.
This strange gauntlet can create a roof light on a tile you're facing; or remove it. It is not able to let you escape, though.
Once planted it spreads roots in every direction.
A vial containing water and rose extract, said to make ones skin silky smooth and hair shiny.
Half of its body is missing but somehow it's still alive. Creepy.
A blob of slime with a tiny crown in its center. With the right headpiece you can reign over all slimes.
Cover up the cold ground and make your base cozy.
A broad stone pillar, depicting an abstract caveling.
A giant, gold-rimmed stone tile, depicting a rendition of the core.
A solid fireplace with heavy mantle. It burns with a strange fire that exits from a gemstone in it's bottom.
An intact stone gate found at the forlorn metropolis. In stands tall and must have dazzled visitors with the giant ancient gemstone in its center.
A stone pedestal with embedded gold and glass, an elegant way to showcase your treasures.
A giant stone slate that seemingly was once part of the ceiling. Tremors must have brought it down.
A toppled entrance made from carved stone and ancient gemstones. It seems to have been part of a sprawling city.
This thick stone tile features a pattern that looks like the core. It has been dislodged from the ground.
Toppled over stone pillars that once supported a very high ceiling. When they fell, they must have caused a lot of destruction.
A large solid shelf with lots of space for books and scrolls. The ones left in it are written in a language you don't speak.
A solid shelf with lots of space for books and scrolls. The ones left in it are unintelligible.
This stool is made from solid stone but has a comfortable cushion embedded.
A big sturdy table hewn from a giant stone slab. There is a lot of space for many people.
A sturdy table hewn from a giant stone slab. There is a lot of space for many people.
This pendant used to look pretty but now it's rusted to the core.
A ring from the depths that someone must have lost long time ago.
A blade so corroded it only vaguely resembles copper. It's deceptively sharp.
Rusted to the core and unusable. That fish was too big to handle, pal.
An old, corroded eating utensil. Almost every culture has invented it.
Scraps tools and equipment you don't need or refurbishes broken ones.
A cursed ring that was used to welcome the cold season into the lands. It represents decay and darkness.
A blessed necklace offered as a gift to farewell the warm season. It represents the harvest and the evening sun.
A very defensive fish with sandstone skin and jagged spikes protruding out.
A warm, soft hat to keep ones ears warm in the cold season. You can't get around wearing one of those in winter.

A fellow caveling that fits in your backpack but wants to be placed down soon because it's eager to work. It will craft presents in exchange for cooked food, give it rare cooked food for higher quality!
Scans the world for Ra-Akar the Sand Titan. Consumed on successful scan.
A masterfully crafted upper body armor to endure the dangers of the desert.
A helm made in the design of Ra-Akar, casting its central eye on your enemies.
A powerful weapon launching explosive projectiles that resemble the center eye of a bomb scarab.
A lower body armor mimicking the properties of desert critters.
The wing carapace of a Bomb Scarab resembling half a skull.
A very advanced anvil for creating supreme equipment.
A valuable ingot for high-tier blacksmithing.
Fierce upper body armor for true warriors.
Used to cross chasms and water but also makes for a nice floor.
A sturdy chest made from scarlet. It is not locked anymore.
The scarlet variant of an iron chunk necklace. It raises your defense even more and gives additional benefits.
A heavy metallic crossbow that shoots potent bolts.
This wavy, crimson dagger pierces through most materials.
A reinforced door to shut out anyone uninvited.
A reinforced metal fence to protect what's rightfully yours.
A tough metal gate for the scarlet fence.
A great tool for pulling up very resistant fish.
A reinforced metal floor tile with a nice crimson alloy.
Menacing-looking horned helm, fits perfectly with the rest of the set.
An excellent tool to prepare ground for farming. Each hit covers an area of 5x5 tiles.
A sturdy key cast in scarlet. There should be a lock somewhere that it fits into.
A great tool for breaking down extremely hard walls.
Scarlet ore commonly found in grass walls.
March through your enemies and don't look back.
A hard-case backpack with lots of space and additional protection.
A very robust shovel, exceptional at digging up ground.
A great weapon for smashing foes and walls.
A great weapon for slaying foes.
Greater workbench to be prepared for the outer cave systems.
A magically-imbued piece of cloth, worn by caveling scholars. Wearing it you feel in tune with the ancients.
Has the comforting smell of musty old books.
A strange hood made from white linen and gold, in its shade you feel more intelligent than usual.
A magical staff wielded by caveling scholars that utilizes an ancient gemstone to produce powerful bolts of energy.
A lifelike representation of a caveling scholar.

Desc: Should be in plural as the ingame icon shows several parts

English: Different materials salvaged from junk. Used to repair items at the salvage and repair station.
A small device made from blue glass, perfectly fitting into your hand. It's touch sensitive and scrolls through images and glyphs.
A translucent ring that looks like a wave frozen in time.
An azure gemstone rarely found in crystalized aquatic regions. Its special properties allow it to be used for higher quality crafting.
A strange shell with a silky-smooth surface.
This box has been created from driftwood and is bleached by light from above.
An unknown liquid slushes inside when shaken. Is there an ancient corkscrew around?
This broken device looks like it was able to predict earthquakes.
A little nutcracker shaped after a core sentry in festive garment. Sadly there are no nuts around to be cracked.
A golden piece of jewelry that's not put onto the finger but rather on the nose.
An ancient crystal shard that is only the fraction of something bigger.
Scans the world for Malugaz the Corrupted. Consumed on successful scan.
A reforged crystal skull that whispers ancient chants. It urges you to place it on the throne room sigil.
A skull covered in ritualistic markings. Its burning eye sockets ignite a fiery fury in you.
This bludgeoning weapon is made from fragile crystal, that can send out splinters when swung.
It's as big as the palm of a hand, meeting with a row of those will end up fatal.
A lifelike representation of a Shrooman Brute.
Don't know where to go? Just look at it!
Someone put all their artistic efforts into painting this sign and left it as a warning. \nCaveling Brutes or worse ahead.
There is no clearer warning than a skull on a stake. Better keep out.
The best way to leave messages for everyone to see.
A modern message sign that can be programmed to display information.
This elusive fish appears in swarms as a spectacle of blinking silver to confuse predators.
Due to its shape, this naturally formed crystal rings with a harmonic frequency when struck.
A spooky scary skeleton made from cheap plastic. Perfect to 'liven' up any room.
The remains of a fellow explorer who wasn't as lucky as you. Funnily enough he can still fit hats onto his pale skull, that's at least something.
A headpiece worn by caveling skirmishers which has been cobbled together with larvaskin, leaves and dirty cloth.
A morbid necklace made from tiny caveling skulls. They're too small to have been children.
A grotesque blood-red ring, crested with a tiny caveling skull.
This ring reminds you of the wide open sky.
A bulbous gemstone that fused many slimes together into a giant one.
Crystal idol to reawaken a Giant Slime. Consumed upon placing it on any Giant Slime summoning rune.
A gelatinous upper body armor that looks like someone dumped a bucket of goo onto you.
An orange blob of slime. Can be further processed.
A gooey, constantly dripping helm that covers half of your face.
A jar filled with slime essence, used for beard care. Place it in a habitable room and a bearded character may move in.
This staff is drenched in slime that never seems to end no matter how much is flung away.
A strange weapon, good for damaging enemies and slowing them down.
A lifelike representation of a common Orange Slime.
Simple ranged weapon to fire away at enemies.
Scans the world for Morpha the Aquatic Mass. Consumed on successful scan.
A blue slime blob almost too slick to hold onto. Can be further processed.
A blue variant of the slime sword. It sometimes spreads slime onto your enemies that makes them slide around.
A small group of long-necked barnacles stretching out from the ground.
A small explosive to blast walls and enemies.
A caveling skull, smaller than usual. It hints at a tragic story.
A strange growth that consists of broad, transparent leaves.
Not a tree at all, but an invertebrate feeding on floating particles with its arms. It hasn't fully matured yet.
Not a tree at all, but an invertebrate feeding on floating particles with its arms. It hasn't fully matured yet.
A weak light to attach to your belt.
This small crystal formation pops and sputters with chaotic energy.
A small, ancient rug caked with the dust of thousands of years. The design on it shows a trinity of eyes.
A kiln that can melt valuable ores.
An old device used to circulate air into a forge to create extreme temperatures. The lever for its mechanism is rusted in place.
Reinforced with several rare materials, this glove can withstand great heat and is a must have for every experienced blacksmith.
Scans the world for the Atlantean Worm. Consumed on successful scan.
A lifelike representation of a Snare Plant.
This little globe has the core as its center and starts a snowfall when shaken.
A handy projectile to start some fights with the neighbours' children. Can also be collected and further processed.
A traditional festive contruct built with snowballs and a light source in the middle.
Whatever one is feeling at the moment, this hat covers it all up with a happy expression made from coal and carrots.
Comfy and lightweight, this poncho flows well as you run.
A stylish hat and scarf, fit for one another.
Comes equipped with winged boots that should aid your mobility.
A soft, squishy sponge. Time to take a bath!
A superior anvil for creating magnificent equipment.
A magnificent ingot for masterful blacksmithing.
A shimmering chest made from solarite. It is not locked anymore.
A grand glimmering crossbow that shoots mighty bolts.
A superior tool for pulling up elusive fish.
A shimmering key cast in solarite. There should be a lock somewhere that it fits into.
A superior tool for breaking down perplexingly hard walls.
An ore that fused with Ancient Gemstones. It can sometimes be found in crystalline walls.
A superior weapon for obliterating foes.
A superior workbench to be prepared for dire trials.
A very defensive fish with rock-hard skin and sharp spikes protruding out.
A robust robe, using magic fused into the fabric to withstand attacks.
A hood worn by Initiated mages.
Sturdy pants with plenty of pockets for magical trinkets.
A vessel with a hot, oil-like substance within.
A depressing stone amulet. You hear whispering...
A magnificent gemstone that glitters in pastel rainbow colors.
A crudely-made rack that is used by cavelings to have their spears at the ready.
Allows travelling over water much faster.
A racing kart with a nice red finish, able to outrace other vehicles after a longer acceleration time. Tends to drift a lot when driving too fast.
A mechanical spike trap that only reacts to enemies.
A ring found at the skeleton of a giant ocean creature. It's made from tiny cervical vertebrae.
A ghastly fish that floats in the air like it's still underwater.
It looks almost too scary to remove its wrapper. What tasty horrors might await behind?
A useful gadget that waters tilled ground in a small radius.
A stone pillar grown over thousands of years through dripping water.
A mysterious living fossil that seems to have fused with precious metals and gemstones to ascend to a higher state of being.
A collection of sparkling colorful crystals. If they grew natural or not remains a mystery.
Used to cross chasms and water but also makes for a nice floor.
Rock-hard mushrooms attached to a stone slate. They look edible but are actually fossilized.
Ground plants found in the Forgotten Ruins. They grow tiny berries that attract cavelings of the corresponding area.
A sturdier door to block out unwanted creatures.
A more reinforced fence to protect what's rightfully yours.
A simple gate for the stone fence.
Simple rock tiles for decorating your base.
An unknown light source sits inside this solid stone cage. The air around it feels cold.
A stone pillar slowly raised over thousands of years through tectonic pressure.
A salty elixir that hardens your skin and makes you more resilient.
The elegant jacket has a stuck-on rose and is perfect for a romantic dinner. Remember to show up on time.
This hat is worn by everyone who considers themself an admirable adventurer equipped with a captivating charisma.
These pants are made from black, silky farbic and hint at sophistication and confidence.
A large bomb harnessing the power of pressurized toxic gas.
This volatile mass latches it's plating onto your body. It feels ready to retaliate.
A sapling grows inside this fragile bulb of toxic gas. The lightest touch can make it burst!
Like a crown, when worn, you assert yourself dominant over the forces within this sulfuric mass.
The gel padding adds a bounce to your step. Suprisingly quiet for the force contained within.
This gnarled tree feasts on the organic matter of the passage. It sprouts glowing sacs of toxic gas.
A lifelike representation of a Sulfur Worm.
Used by great mages to conjure small stars.
Nothing is more important than sporting cool sunglasses, even when it's dark.
A vibrant crop that braces you for tough encounters.
A very rare variant of the common sunrice.
Grows into a bracing crop when planted. Only grows in crystal ground.
A large group of two coral species that grow together to form a symbiosis.
A group of two coral species that grow together to form a symbiosis.
A small group of two coral species that grow together to form a symbiosis.
A large branchy coral that provides protection and food for small sea critters.
A small branchy coral that provides protection and food for small sea critters.
A large coral that develops a wide brim above the water surface, providing a safe island for small organisms.
A small coral that develops a wide brim above the water surface, providing a safe island for small organisms.
A fragile butterfly that has been completely corrupted by crystals.
A mysterious feather that allows you to dash out of danger.
Wearing this winged ring creates a slight wind that pushes you forward.
Wearing those chill blue shorts tempts you to constantly form the shaka sign with your hand.
Wearing those chill green shorts tempts you to constantly form the shaka sign with your hand.
Wearing those chill red shorts tempts you to constantly form the shaka sign with your hand.
A simple saw to cut materials into slates. Requires electricity.
A large group of long-necked barnacles stretching out from the ground.
A tall, strange growth that consists of broad, transparent leaves.
A large patch of tall grass to use as a decorative.
A large type of algae that can grow outside of water.
This wooden chest-piece is wrapped in a bundle of mysteriously unwithering leaves.
A wooden mask with decorative leaves and horns attuned to the wildlife.
An animalistic emblem decorated with golden trinkets that ring out to the wild.
Leafy legwear made from ancient wooden roots that seem to connect with the earth whenever one stands still.
A wooden ring with two smaller rings around it. One symbolises the warden and the other the bonded beast.
A greenish-blue, odd-looking fish with weirdly shaped fins.
This decorative vase has been made in honor of Azeos, the Sky Titan.
A block made from hazy blue glass with golden etchings. The information written on it is lost forever as it has been smashed on purpose.
A block made from hazy blue glass with golden etchings. It seems like these were used as memorials or to mark places of importance.
An ancient sandstone wall with an angled top and covered in indecipherable glyphs. What stories do they tell?
An ancient sandstone wall covered in indecipherable glyphs. What stories do they tell?
This intimidating statue depicts an ancient guardian in exotic garment. Its kneeling pose hints at being in service of a king.
A statue wilfully destroyed by grave thiefs. It has been partially relieved of the green daggers in its stony clasp.
This decorative vase has been made in honor of Omoroth, the Sea Titan.
An ancient golden stand that seems to have held royal belongings once.
A very beautiful, decorative pillar only found in ancient desert temples.
A load-bearing pillar which holds up the foundation of the ancient desert temples.
This decorative vase has been made in honor of Ra-Akar, the Sand Titan.
A golden throne reserved only for the buttocks of ancient royalty.
This ancient trap shoots projectiles at anyone walking into its line of sight. Its inner workings are concealed by a caveling grimace.
A dried piece of tentacle. It's quite tough and keeps your teeth busy.
A lifelike representation of a Tentacle.
An elastic tentacle that lashes out at enemies from afar. It's still alive and wiggling in your hand.
The mutated offspring of its extinct ancestor. Its brown shell had adapted to withstand extreme pressure.
A thin wall made from glass, perfect to create enclosures.
A brambly variant of the common root wood.
A set of curved blades. They're evenly balanced so that throwing them is as easy as pointing a finger.
A strange apparatus that sends shockwaves deep into the ground. Using it at the right spot may awaken something from its slumber. Is consumed on successful use.
An empty grave that has been moved out of its alignment in search for valuables.
An intact hourglass, filled with blue sand. It is not clear what period of time it measures, as the sand seems to fall incredibly slowly.
A better anvil for creating gear and weapons more suited for survival.
A slower but more damaging weapon against multiple enemies.
A tough metal ingot for blacksmithing.
A good armor to survive battles more easily.
A small blade that allows for quick stabs.
A durable tool for pulling up bigger fish.
This helm repels slight blows to the head.
A durable tool to prepare ground for farming. Covers an area of 3x3 tiles.
A durable tool, good for breaking down walls more easily.
A durable shovel, well-suited for digging up ground.
A bulky weapon for smashing foes and walls.
A sharp weapon for slaying foes.
A better workbench to prepare you for the underground world.
A vile treatise on the conjuring of dark spirits.
Powerful incantions barely utterable by the human tongue.
More of a pamphlet, beginners guide to shadowmancy.
A precious little ring with a yellow gemstone on top.
A piece of jewelry for the neck that's merely a hoop with a gap. Worn by many different cultures throughout world history.
Light up your surroundings. Can also be placed on the ground and attached to walls.
An extremely rare enigma of sea life that seems to unify all other fish beneath it.
A towel is about the most massively useful thing an underground miner can have.
A necklace featuring a coiling shell. Its ever turning spiral structure is captivating.
A coat with deep pockets fit for a hoggish, dodgy fancier.
A strange gold piece vibrating with energy.

A symbiosis of an ancient gemstone with organic matter, resulting in a physically impossible material. It pulsates in energetic rhythms of three, a celestial pattern that must have been of utter importance to a spacefaring species.
The petrified remains of a species that still exists to this day, even after 220 million years.
A young that comes up from the ground once it had enough time to slumber in the dark. Its shell is still blank but in time it will be populated by the kelp that it feeds on.

A marine reptile and natural gardener, that chews down on kelp when it grows too plenty. It doesn't need many nutrients, so whatever it eats comes out again in a condensed ball shape that is free for the taking.
A hard shell that once belonged to a graceful sea creature. You feel much more protected when holding it.
A green gem shaped like a spiral.
A lifelike representation of the Unleashed Core Commander.
An intricate, unique chest with a purple gemstone locked in its center.
An intricate, unique chest with an orange gemstone locked in its center.
An intricate, unique chest with a green gemstone locked in its center.
A two-component potion that is risky to drink.
A high-tech workbench to upgrade tools and weapons, making them stronger and more effective.
A handful of small, pink candles that fill the air with a whiff of vanille.
This heart-themed chest is great to tuck away little trinkets of love.
This little paper bag contains enough rose petals to cover a 1x1 floor tile with them. Great to lay out a path of love.
A scented letter that contains words of love and appreciation. Give it to someone in dire need of affection.
A golden necklace featuring a big, shiny heart. You feel something you can't describe, when wearing it so close to your own.
A simple painting showing nothing more than a heart. Sometimes this is all one needs in these dark times.
A big plushie, resembling a caveling brute holding a heart. Even those need a little bit of love sometimes.
This rose and silver-colored gift is packed with a variety of different charming items.
A golden ring featuring a candy-colored heart. The perfect gift to give to someone you like.
Nothing speaks 'love' like a big fuzzy heart on the floor. It smells like wool and lavender.
An assortment of hearts cut from paper, they look great on walls and make a base just a little bit more lovely.
A workbench containing tools and blueprints to create some beautiful decorative items.
A black satin cape fit for a vampire. The crimson flip-up collar adds to the evil look.
A bloodsucking fish latching onto everything that has a pulse.
A broken automaton that once contained snacks and other goods. It looks like it was forced open.
An old, still functioning automaton that is proof of advanced technology and a sophisticated society.
This draconic fish has green scales that can withstand remarkably high temperatures.
The unsettling gaze of this ring causes minions to stay on high alert.
A particle weapon with unknown inner workings. It emits balls of void that distort spacetime to inflict high damage.
A mysterious intricate piece of architecture.
A large chest, made from the hardened mass of the gargantuan amoeba. You feel uneasy in its presence.
Scans the world for Urschleim. Consumed on successful scan.
A highly mutative, crystalized cell. To resummon Urschleim, activate it in the Passage where ancient lifeforms still roam. Consumed in the process.

Desc: For translating the name 'Urschleim' reference back to the note I left in the 'Names' bracket of this document

English: A sturdy piece of city architecture, decorated with glass and gold.
A red, wet piece of clay.
A blue, glistening piece of crystal.
A sturdy dark piece of stone.
A sandy piece of desert stone.
An extremely durable block used to build ancient mazes.
A sturdy piece of ancient architecture, decorated with tiles and gold.
A brown solid piece of dirt.
A highly dangerous box of explosives that can be placed like a wall. Don't hit it or it will blow up right in your face.
An otherwordly wall speckled with glittering stars.
A solid wall made from glass. Works well for building a base or enclosures.
An enigmatic wall reinforced with glimmering plates.
A lush piece of vertical plants.
A lumpy… living piece of hive material.
A sandy piece of the coastal stone.
A mellow piece of earth with little summer flowers growing on it.
An unstable, explosive piece of wall.
An indestructible piece of obsidian. You're not supposed to have this…
A bleak stone wall ready to be turned lively with colors.
Layers upon layers of living matter have been crushed into a dense, twisted mass.
A yellow fragile piece of sand.
A reinforced metal wall to set up your base for tough encounters.
A white cold piece of snow.
A solid wall made with interlocking blocks.
A reinforced straw wall to set up a cozy farm.
A soft mossy piece of turf.
A solid wall made from wood. Works well for building a base.
A container used to store water and filling up watering cans.
Used to water seeds and soil.
A large seaweed that lives off of the light cast down into the wilderness.
A floating plant that is part of a rich aquatic ecosystem.
An ancient stone well to take water from.
A miraculous gemstone device used to teleport to other waypoints and portals. When placed, it takes 10 minutes to charge up before it can be accessed.
A simple, white dress elevating the beauty of its wearer. There are many occasions to wear it but the most important one is being a bride.
A beautiful crown made from leaves and pink roses. It resembles a love that feels like eternal spring.
A broken wheelbarrow stuck in its own molten contents. It seems like it couldn't withstand the extreme heat.
A silky white blossom that fell from a beautiful tree. In full bloom it has a faint almond fragrance and reminds one of the joys of life.
This beautiful white tree is a traditional symbol of the joys of life. It is said that in spring a fairy maiden descends to awake the sleeping cherry trees with her breath.
A small white amphibian with outward-protruding gills that look like corals. It also uses them to draw nutrients out of the waters of the Sunken Sea.
This ring is made from a milky, translucent material. The light it reflects makes it harder for enemies to hit you.
This beautiful bouquet made from white roses will elevate the look of every room. Give it to someone you like dearly.
A rare artifact made from precious, white stone. It doesn't produce a sound when you try to use it.
This golden and white bell produces a fine ringing sound, it's faint and reminds one of falling snow.
Nicely decorated this handful of cookies will put one in a seasonal mood. There's even a little core-shaped one in there.
A full meal to warm your belly in the cold season. Prepared with a roasted larva, hot heartberry sauce, dumplings and some greens.
A worn vest with a simple shirt underneath.
A rustic top hat with various trinkets along the brim.
A pair of jeans with a golden chain strapped on.
A crude bow to shoot foes from afar.
Very crude armor for the upper body. Offers minor protection.
Used to cross chasms and water but also makes for a nice floor.
A small wooden crossbow that swiftly shoots bolts.
A piece of giant root to create all sorts of things.
Close up your base with this simple door.
A simple fence to protect what's rightfully yours.
A simple gate for the wooden fence.
A crude tool for pulling up fish.
Simple wooden slats for decorating your base.
Slight protection for the head but you should look for better options soon.
A crude tool to prepare ground for farming.
A crude tool, useful for breaking down walls.
The next best thing when it comes to lower body armor.
This decorative, wooden pillar is just the basic design for a whole lot more colorful variants.
A useful off-hand item to block hits from enemies.
A crude shovel, useful for digging up ground.
A crude spike trap that only reacts to enemies.
A simple, workable stool made from wood. A true hobbyist might turn this into something more beautiful.
A crude weapon to fend off foes.
A simple, workable table made from wood. A true hobbyist might turn this into something more beautiful.
A wooden box used by someone to store random goods.
A simple wooden ring, nothing more, nothing less.
Driftwood with patterns and carvings showing the Core.
Driftwood with patterns and carvings showing a Glow Tulip.
A circular, brambly root with sharp thorns pointing outward.
The most basic of all workbenches.
An incredibly soft tuft of wool that has a pleasant scent to it.
Cast from thick metal this tool seemed to be attached to a chain. Has it been used to keep the unlawful from running away?

Grabbing cooked food from the cooking pot increases the chance of gaining additional cooked food.
Crafting items increases your physical durability.
Reeling up fish or other treasures from waters increases your fishing skill.
Harvesting plants gives you green fingers, allowing you to gain extra plants.

Summoned minions that attack improves your minions damage.

The soul of Azeos empowers you with the ancient thunder.
The soul of Omoroth empowers you with the forces of the depth.
The soul of Ra-Akar empowers you with the ancient force of the desert.
The soul of Druidra imbues you with the enduring vitality of the ancient forests.
The soul of Crydra engulfs you in the protective embrace of the ocean's depths.
The soul of Pyrdra ignites your spirit with the unyielding fury of liquid stone.
In return,* thou shalt be able to go back to whence thou camest.
By the power with which we now imbue thee, the Great Wall shall be opened as thou layest a hand upon it.
Never have we seen a creature such as thee.
There once was a thriving civilization here, but it seems all of it has been lost.
We must have been dormant for aeons.
We must ask something of thee.
Seek the ancient titans still roaming beyond the Great Wall.
Destroy them and collect their souls.
With their energy we can restore what once was.
Our world... long ago hath been erased.
This one we discovered, amidst a multitude.
Yet there exists no room for thee in our rekindled society.
Another world... which hath expelled us.
Or... was it the unity of its inhabitants?
Thee strength is why thy must perish!
...come to us ...the barren place far to the {0}...
...find us at the origin of this world...
Thou hast achieved the seeming impossible.
Only through collective spirit could such powers be harnessed.
With these, we may at last restore what once hath been.
Come to us, unto the place where we once set our roots in this world.
This instrument, it hath fulfilled its purpose.
**There was a presence. **It hath now departed.
With our combined efforts I shall return thee to where thou camest.
If ever thou findst your way hither again, let us be a force for brilliance.
